Prekoruplje (Albanian: Prekorupa, Llapusha, Serbian Cyrillic: Прекорупље) is a geographical and ethnographical region in Kosovo, including the eastern portion of the larger Metohija region which includes the western part of Kosovo. It is located between Podgor, Podrimlje, Drenica and Lapušnik. It stretches mainly over the basin area of two rivers, lower Klina and Miruša, and includes ca. 40 settlements. Orahovac is the centre of Prekoruplje. Today, the area is predominantly inhabited by Albanians.
